                        <locus>1r-35v</locus>
                        <author ref="#hyginus">Hyginus</author>
                        <title ref="#de_astronomia">De astronomia</title>
                        <decoNote>Illustrations of the constellations to the second book in red ink, no stars marked; some initials to open paragraphs and more elaborated ones at the beginning of books; marginal headings for separate sections (e.g. De lacteo circulo). Illustrations drawn after the text was written (in some cases the red ink traced over the brown ink of the text).</decoNote>
                    </msItem>
                    <msItem>
                        <locus>35v</locus>
                        <note type="title">Later addition: two prayers.</note>
                    </msItem>
                    <!--  
When illustrations are to the second mythologycal book - interest in the stories (also no stars marked?) 

Light book; looks more like the personal endeavour (perhaps one scribe?) to be read alone; as the language is simple - no need of glossing (there are no glosses; no corrections either)  

Used thick parchment, here and there some tiny holes and sewing ; but in the same time made some effort to have nice initials and orientation in the text. Left space for the illustration in the second book. 

 -->
